description:
Gap found: link_ctx initialization in iface_init not verified against prior state.

Why this was missed: iface_init assumed clean state.

The actual bug: Line 959 calls lichen_link_init(&link_ctx, eui64) without first checking if link_ctx was previously initialized. If lichen_l2_iface_init() is called twice (shouldn't happen via NET_DEVICE_INIT, but could via manual call), the old link_ctx state is overwritten without cleanup.

Potential issues:
1. If link_ctx contains dynamically allocated state, it would leak
2. If link_ctx has active sequence numbers, they are lost (could cause replay false positives)

The static link_ctx at module scope starts zeroed (BSS), so first init is safe. Double-init would be a programming error.

Compare with lichen_l2_enable() at line 708 which does secure_zero(&link_ctx) before re-init.

Priority 3 - defensive cleanup should be added for consistency:
  if (atomic_get(&link_ctx_initialized)) {
      lichen_link_cleanup(&link_ctx);
  }
  lichen_link_init(&link_ctx, eui64);
